The officer Lambert stated that Ward had been committed to Five Years' Penal Servitude, and broke out of prison and committed a burglary on the same night; and Thomas Barking, Police Inspector, stated that a case of three burglaries in Kennington had been remanded until after this trial, as there were footmarks in the gardens of the houses corresponding with the prisoners.—<rs id="t18650130-268-punishment-41" type="punishmentDescription">
